The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 CMC posts 20% jump in revenues

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, April 15: CMC Ltd, a subsidiary of Tata Consultancy Services Ltd (TCS) that provides information technology solutions, today posted a 20.54 per cent jump in revenues, from Rs 215.45 crore in the fourth quarter of 2004-05 to Rs 259.71 crore in the same quarter of the last financial year. 

 The company closed the financial year 2005-06 with revenues of Rs 857.75 compared with Rs 782.47 in the previous year. The company registered an after-tax profit of Rs 8.55 crore in the fourth quarter compared with Rs 16.72 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company earned other income of Rs 2,46.58 crore from profit on sale of land and residential properties.

 Consolidated results comprise consolidation of the financial results of CMC Ltd and its wholly owned subsidiary CMC Americas Inc. The CMC board has also proposed a dividend of Rs 5 per share subject to approval at the annual general meeting. 

 In October 2001, Tata Sons acquired a 51 per cent stake in CMC Ltd. TCS, the software services division of Tata Sons, had proposed to begin the process of strengthening its position in the Indian software services industry through this acquisition. 

 Tata Sons had, consequently, come out with an open offer to acquire another 16.69 per cent stake in the company at Rs 281.26 per share. 




